==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Dado
<hw>Da"do</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Dadoes</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[It. <ets>dado</ets> die,
cube, pedestal; of the same origin as E. <ets>die</ets>, <ets>n.</ets>
See <er>Die</er>, <pos>n.</pos>]</ety> <fld>(Arch.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd>
<def>That part of a pedestal included between the base and the cornice
(or surbase); the die. See <xex>Illust.</xex> of <er>Column</er>.</def>
Hence: <sd>(b)</sd> <def>In any wall, that part of the basement included
between the base and the base course. See <cref>Base course</cref>,
under <er>Base</er>.</def> <sd>(c)</sd> <def>In interior decoration, the
lower part of the wall of an apartment when adorned with moldings, or
otherwise specially decorated.</def></p>

